    "text":  "but no matter where she went, that glaring beam of light followed, along with the cheers of her classmates: \"SPEECH! SPEECH! SPEECH!\" She didn\u0027t even see Tiana until she had run into her, sending Tiana\u0027s armful of art supplies flying. Margot dropped to the floor and began to pick up the fallen paints and brushes. \"I\u0027m so sorry!\" she blurted out. It was the first time she had spoken to any of her classmates. She cringed, but Tiana just knelt down next to her. \"It\u0027s okay,\" Tiana said. \"Wow, it\u0027s nice to finally talk to you.\" Margot lifted her head. \"Aren\u0027t you angry at me?\" she asked. \"Not at all—it was an accident,\"",
